#: src/preferences.c:2335
msgid ""
"<b>Error correction method</b>\n"
"\n"
"dvdisaster creates error correction data which is used to recover unreadable sectors if the disc becomes damaged later on. There are different codecs and ways available for storing the error correction information:\n"
msgstr "<b>Error correction method</b>\n\ndvdisaster creates error correction data which is used to recover unreadable sectors if the disc becomes damaged later on. There are different codecs and ways available for storing the error correction information:\n"

#: src/preferences.c:2341
msgid ""
"The RS01 codec\n"
"RS01 is the recommended codec for storing error correction data in separate files.\n"
msgstr "The RS01 codec\nRS01 is the recommended codec for storing error correction data in separate files.\n"

#: src/preferences.c:2344
msgid ""
"The RS02 codec\n"
"RS02 is the currently recommended codec for augmenting images with error correction data.\n"
msgstr "The RS02 codec\nRS02 is the currently recommended codec for augmenting images with error correction data.\n"

#: src/preferences.c:2348
msgid ""
"The RS03 codec (Warning: experimental)\n"
"RS03 can either store error correction data in a separate file or augment the image with it. It provides multithreading to scale with multicore processors and contains some subtle improvements over RS01 and RS02. However it should not be used for productive work unless a stable version is released with dvdisaster V0.80."
msgstr "The RS03 codec (Warning: experimental)\nRS03 can either store error correction data in a separate file or augment the image with it. It provides multithreading to scale with multicore processors and contains some subtle improvements over RS01 and RS02. However it should not be used for productive work unless a stable version is released with dvdisaster V0.80."

